# AI Chief of Staff: Visual Design for Neurodivergent Users

## Core Design Philosophy
**Gentle Novelty System** - Every view has subtle, non-repeating animations that evolve over 24-hour cycles without distracting. Visual elements have organic, non-mechanical motion with variations in timing curves to prevent pattern recognition.

**Global Specifications**
- **Screen**: 55" 4K (3840×2160), optimal viewing distance 1.5-3m
- **Color Palette**: 
  - Background: `#0A0E14` (deep space blue, not pure black)
  - Primary: `#4ECDC4` (turquoise), `#FF6B6B` (coral for urgent)
  - Secondary: `#556B8D` (muted blue), `#C7F464` (lime for positive)
  - Accent: `#FFD166` (gold), `#9D4EDD` (purple)
- **Typography**: 
  - Headline: "Inter Display" Semibold (high legibility, geometric)
  - Body: "Inter" Regular/Medium
  - Glance-scale: 64px min, Look-scale: 32px min, Read-scale: 24px min
- **Animation Principles**: Spring physics (custom easing), duration 300-800ms, never linear timing

---

## 1. AMBIENT VIEW: "Constellation Flow"

**Concept**: A living starfield where each star represents a business entity (person, project, company). Constellations form and dissolve based on relationship strength. System health encoded in nebula colors.

**Layout**:
- Full-screen particle system (10,000-15,000 particles at 4K)
- Density gradient: more particles toward center (focal area)
- Bottom 15%: subtle status bar with time/date/glance metrics

**Visual Elements**:
```css
/* Particle properties */
.particle {
  position: absolute;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: radial-gradient(circle, 
    var(--particle-color) 0%, 
    transparent 70%);
  opacity: 0.3-0.8;
  size: 2-8px;
  filter: blur(0.5px);
  animation: float 15-25s infinite alternate ease-in-out;
}

/* Constellation connections */
.connection {
  stroke: rgba(78, 205, 196, 0.15);
  stroke-width: 0.5;
  stroke-dasharray: 3, 3;
  animation: pulse 8s infinite;
}
```

**Behavior & Novelty**:
- Particles have 3 movement algorithms (swarm, flow, orbit) that rotate every 2 hours
- Nebula background shifts through 5 color moods (dawn, day, dusk, night, storm) based on system load
- Every 47 minutes, a "shooting star" streaks toward a pending item
- Constellation patterns reform every 30 minutes based on priority relationships
- Particle brightness pulses gently with user's calendar rhythm (meetings = quicker pulses)

**Transition to other views**: Constellations gather toward center, form the logo, then dissolve into next view (800ms)

---

## 2. BRIEFING VIEW: "Narrative Horizon"

**Concept**: A panoramic, cinematic presentation of information. Text appears in focused "blocks" that scroll horizontally like a film credit sequence, with visual anchors for each topic.

**Layout**:
- Split-screen: Left 40% for visual timeline, Right 60% for narrative
- Visual timeline: vertical flow of icons + time indicators
- Narrative area: single-column text with generous margins

**Typography**:
```css
.briefing-headline {
  font-family: 'Inter Display', sans-serif;
  font-weight: 600;
  font-size: 72px;
  line-height: 1.1;
  margin-bottom: 40px;
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, #4ECDC4, #9D4EDD);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
}

.briefing-paragraph {
  font-size: 32px;
  line-height: 1.6;
  margin: 30px 0;
  max-width: 45ch;
  opacity: 0;
  animation: paragraph-reveal 0.8s forwards;
}

@keyframes paragraph-reveal {
  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); }
  to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
}
```

**Progressive Disclosure**:
1. **Glance (1s)**: Headline + 3 key metrics (large, centered)
2. **Look (5s)**: Headline + first paragraph + timeline visualization
3. **Engage (30s)**: Full narrative with interactive timeline - tap any event to expand details

**Visual Timeline**:
- Vertical line down left side with circular nodes
- Each node has unique icon + color based on category
- Hovering node highlights related text in narrative
- Timeline scrolls at different speed than text (parallax effect)

**Animation**: Paragraphs fade in sequentially with 300ms delay. Timeline nodes pulse when their content becomes visible. Horizontal scroll of narrative area at 50px/second (adjustable).

---

## 3. ACTION VIEW: "Decision Sphere"

**Concept**: Entire screen focuses on one action. Information radiates from center decision point. No competing visual elements.

**Layout**:
- Central circle (40% of screen) containing core decision/question
- Concentric rings containing context (inner), implications (middle), options (outer)
- Bottom: action buttons (large, high contrast)

**Visual Treatment**:
```css
.decision-core {
  width: 800px;
  height: 800px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: radial-gradient(circle at 30% 30%,
    rgba(78, 205, 196, 0.1) 0%,
    transparent 70%);
  border: 3px solid rgba(78, 205, 196, 0.3);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  animation: gentle-pulse 4s infinite alternate;
}

.core-text {
  font-size: 64px;
  text-align: center;
  max-width: 20ch;
  padding: 40px;
}

.context-ring {
  position: absolute;
  border-radius: 50%;
  border: 1px dashed rgba(255, 107, 107, 0.3);
  animation: rotate-slow 120s linear infinite;
}
```

**Urgency Encoding**:
- Low urgency: Blue tones, slower pulse (8s), calm rotation
- Medium: Gold tones, medium pulse (4s)
- High: Coral tones with slight vibration (not jittery), faster pulse (2s)
- Critical: Gentle red glow that breaths (1.5s pulse)

**Interaction**: Options appear as arcs around the circle. Gaze detection (via webcam) highlights option user looks at. Voice confirmation available.

**Transition**: From ambient view, particles coalesce into the decision sphere (600ms).

---

## 4. THREAD VIEW: "Story River"

**Concept**: Horizontal timeline that flows like a river. Events are "islands" in the stream. Narrative flows left-to-right, depth indicates importance.

**Layout**:
- Horizontal scrolling timeline (10x screen width)
- Central river flows with varying width (based on activity density)
- Events placed above/below timeline based on type (email=below, meeting=above)
- Vertical cross-section shows depth of engagement at any point

**Visual Encoding**:
```css
.timeline-river {
  height: 120px;
  background: linear-gradient(90deg,
    transparent,
    rgba(78, 205, 196, 0.1) 20%,
    rgba(78, 205, 196, 0.2) 50%,
    rgba(78, 205, 196, 0.1) 80%,
    transparent);
  border-radius: 60px;
  animation: flow 30s linear infinite;
  background-size: 200% 100%;
}

.event-node {
  width: 80px;
  height: 80px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  position: absolute;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  filter: drop-shadow(0 5px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.3));
  transition: all 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1);
}

.event-node:hover {
  transform: scale(1.3);
  z-index: 100;
}
```

**Event Types**:
- **Email**: Flat disc below timeline, color by sender importance
- **Meeting**: 3D sphere above timeline, size by duration
- **Document**: Cube shape, rotation indicates revision status
- **Decision**: Diamond shape, glow effect
- **Claude Session**: Hexagon with animated thinking dots

**Story Visualization**:
- River width expands during intense periods
- Tributaries branch off for sub-threads
- Water "ripples" flow from recent events downstream
- Click any event: radial detail view appears without leaving context

**Navigation**: Swipe gesture or voice ("show me last week"). Auto-scroll to most recent with option to pause.

---

## 5. HEALTH VIEW: "Relationship Garden"

**Concept**: People represented as interactive plants in a ecosystem. Health = plant vitality. Proximity = relationship strength.

**Layout**:
- Isometric garden view (45° angle)
- Each person has a dedicated "plot" with consistent position
- Floating labels appear on hover
- Weather system above represents overall relationship climate

**Visual Design**:
```css
.person-plant {
  position: absolute;
  transition: all 0.6s cubic-bezier(0.68, -0.55, 0.27, 1.55);
}

.plant-stem {
  width: 8px;
  background: linear-gradient(to top, #4CAF50, #8BC34A);
  height: var(--health-height); /* 60-200px based on relationship health */
}

.plant-leaves {
  width: 60px;
  height: 60px;
  background: radial-gradient(circle at 30% 30%,
    var(--person-color) 0%,
    transparent 70%);
  border-radius: 50% 50% 50% 0;
  transform: rotate(45deg);
  animation: sway 8s infinite alternate ease-in-out;
}

.health-flower {
  /* Only blooms when relationship score > 80 */
  opacity: calc((var(--score) - 80) / 20);
}
```

**Health Indicators**:
- **Plant height**: Overall relationship strength (taller = stronger)
- **Leaf color**: Recent interaction frequency (greener = more recent)
- **Flowers**: Positive sentiment (blooms with positivity)
- **Soil moisture**: Communication balance (dry = you talk more, wet = they talk more)
- **Butterflies**: Mutual benefits present (fluttering around healthy relationships)

**Interaction**: 
- Click plant: detailed metrics appear as floating cards
- Drag plants together: visualize potential connections
- Weather changes: "sunny" for healthy network, "clouds" for attention needed

**Animation**: Gentle swaying (different periods per plant). Butterflies follow L-system paths. Occasional "growth spurts" when relationships improve.

---

## TRANSITION SYSTEM

**Principles**: Never abrupt. Always contextual.

```css
.view-transition {
  animation: view-change 800ms cubic-bezier(0.76, 0, 0.24, 1);
}

@keyframes view-change {
  0% { opacity: 1; }
  20% { opacity: 0.3; } /* Brief fade */
  100% { opacity: 1; }
}

/* View-specific transitions */
.ambient-to-briefing {
  /* Particles form words then scatter */
}

.briefing-to-action {
  /* Text collapses into center point, then expands as sphere */
}
```

**Voice Integration**: "Show me [view name]" triggers transition with additional auditory cue (subtle tonal sound).

---

## ADHD-SPECIFIC ADAPTATIONS

1. **Novelty Engine**: 
   - Color schemes rotate every 3 days (6 palettes)
   - Particle behaviors change weekly (swarm, wave, spiral)
   - Unexpected "easter eggs" on milestone achievements

2. **Focus Support**:
   - Gentle halo effect around most important element
   - Peripheral elements desaturate slightly when not needed
   - Optional "focus mode" simplifies any view to 3 elements max

3. **Reduced Distraction**:
   - All animations below 0.3Hz (slow, natural rhythms)
   - No sudden movements or flashing
   - Consistent spatial positioning (muscle memory)

4. **Engagement Hooks**:
   - Micro-progress animations (like growing vines for completed tasks)
   - Surprise celebratory effects for completed major items
   - Seasonal themes that change monthly

This system creates a living artifact that rewards attention without demanding it—evolving enough to maintain novelty but stable enough to build familiarity. The organic motions and game-like visual metaphors create an experience that feels more like observing a ecosystem than monitoring a dashboard.

# Laptop Activity Monitoring System Design

## **Recommended Architecture: Hybrid Approach**

**Primary:** Option 1 (Accessibility API) + Option 2 (Lightweight Daemon)
**Supplemental:** Option 5 (Calendar Integration)

### **Assessment of Options**

**1. macOS Accessibility API**
- **Privacy:** Requires explicit user permission via Security & Privacy settings. Only captures app/window data.
- **Performance:** Minimal impact - event-driven (triggers only on window/app changes)
- **Reliability:** High - direct system API
- **Information:** Active app + window title (rich context source)
- **Display Reaction:** Immediate updates on context changes

**2. Lightweight Daemon**
- **Privacy:** Controlled data sharing - only what's needed for display
- **Performance:** Minimal - 30s intervals or event-driven POSTs
- **Reliability:** Network dependent, implement retry with backoff
- **Information:** Customizable JSON payload
- **Display Reaction:** Consistent periodic updates

**3. AppleScript Polling**
- **Privacy:** Also needs accessibility permissions
- **Performance:** Moderate - polling adds overhead
- **Reliability:** Medium - script may hang or timeout
- **Information:** App name only (limited)
- **Display Reaction:** Delayed updates (polling interval)

**4. Screen Time Data**
- **Privacy:** Very private (aggregated, delayed)
- **Performance:** Low - reading local database
- **Reliability:** High but delayed (not real-time)
- **Information:** Historical usage patterns
- **Display Reaction:** Background trend analysis only

**5. Calendar Integration**
- **Privacy:** Calendar data only, user controls sharing
- **Performance:** Negligible
- **Reliability:** High via Google Calendar API
- **Information:** Scheduled meetings, free/busy
- **Display Reaction:** Meeting context enhancement

---

## **System Implementation**

### **Laptop Daemon: "AmbientAgent"**

```python
# ~/Library/Application Support/AmbientAgent/ambient_monitor.py
import json
import time
import requests
from AppKit import NSWorkspace, NSApplicationActivationPolicy
from Cocoa import NSObject, NSDistributedNotificationCenter
from datetime import datetime, timedelta
import subprocess

class ActivityMonitor(NSObject):
    def __init__(self):
        self.last_activity = datetime.now()
        self.last_app = ""
        self.last_title = ""
        self.mac_mini_url = "http://mac-mini.local:8080/activity"
        self.secret_token = "<generated-shared-token>"

    def send_activity(self, app_name, window_title, is_idle=False, is_sleeping=False):
        payload = {
            "timestamp": datetime.now().isoformat(),
            "app": app_name,
            "window_title": window_title,
            "is_idle": is_idle,
            "is_sleeping": is_sleeping,
            "device_id": "macbook-pro-primary"
        }

        headers = {
            "Authorization": f"Bearer {self.secret_token}",
            "Content-Type": "application/json"
        }

        try:
            requests.post(self.mac_mini_url, json=payload, headers=headers, timeout=2)
        except:
            # Queue for retry
            pass

    def get_active_window(self):
        # Get frontmost app
        active_app = NSWorkspace.sharedWorkspace().frontmostApplication()
        app_name = active_app.localizedName() if active_app else ""

        # Get window title via AppleScript
        script = '''
        tell application "System Events"
            set frontApp to first application process whose frontmost is true
            set windowName to name of front window of frontApp
            return windowName
        end tell
        '''

        try:
            result = subprocess.run(['osascript', '-e', script], 
                                  capture_output=True, text=True)
            window_title = result.stdout.strip() if result.returncode == 0 else ""
        except:
            window_title = ""

        return app_name, window_title

    def check_idle_time(self):
        # Check last input activity
        script = '''
        set idleTime to (do shell script "ioreg -c IOHIDSystem | awk '/HIDIdleTime/ {print $NF/1000000000; exit}'")
        return idleTime
        '''
        # Returns idle time in seconds
        # If > 600 (10 min), trigger idle mode

    def monitor_loop(self):
        while True:
            # Check for sleep/clamshell mode
            if self.is_laptop_asleep():
                self.send_activity("", "", False, True)
                time.sleep(30)
                continue

            # Check idle
            idle_seconds = self.check_idle_time()
            is_idle = idle_seconds > 600

            if not is_idle:
                app_name, window_title = self.get_active_window()

                # Only send if changed
                if app_name != self.last_app or window_title != self.last_title:
                    self.send_activity(app_name, window_title, False, False)
                    self.last_app = app_name
                    self.last_title = window_title
                    self.last_activity = datetime.now()

            time.sleep(30)  # 30-second intervals
```

